    parentName: "p",
    "href": "https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2016/02/how-mit-students-gamed-the-lottery/470349/"
  }, "312,000 by one syndicate leader\u2019s account"), ") and shifted the statistics in their favor, letting them win more than they lose. In a ballsy move, one syndicate from MIT bought 700,000 tickets\u2014in a single week\u2014to \u201Cpush\u201D the jackpot over $2 million earlier than expected\u2014they made off with nearly the entire jackpot and pocketed $700,000 in profit."), mdx("p", null, "How does this relate to machine learning? As an applied scientist, machine learning is the game, applying it in industry is the metagame. When I first started, I found a ", mdx("strong", {
